						               													<description>A Means of Peace is a free supplement to the Napoleonics ruleset He Did What Heroes Do.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Even with some changes in technology, armies in the American Civil War were remarkably similar to their European counteparts from the start of the century.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game continues to focus on command and control; you will still be ordering around divisions but the nature of the fighting is even more brutal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You will need the base rule set to use this product.&amp;#10;The turns continue as normal, but there are a few special rules that will affect play. &amp;#10;The standard system of orders, Initiative and combat is fairly unchanged.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Designed to be played with 2 to 6mm, but can be adapted to other scales.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
